<HEADLINE>
PREMIER VOWS TO CONTINUE TOURISM, AIRLINK TALKS WITH CHINA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May  31 (CNA) 05/31/07  14:17:43 (By Sofia Wu)
</P>
<P>
Premier Chang Chun-hsiung will assure lawmakers in his first
administrative report to the legislature of the government's
determination to complete negotiations with China over opening to
Chinese tourists and inauguration of regular charter flights
across the Taiwan Strait as early as possible, sources said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chang is scheduled to brief lawmakers on his Cabinet's work
agenda and take questions from them Friday for the first time
since he assumed premiership May 21. The written version of his
report was referred to the Legislative Yuan Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the written report, Premier Chang said the country
is facing certain difficult problems that require patience,
wisdom and inter-party cooperation to resolve.
</P>
<P>
Chang said he will work hard to consult with opposition parties
in order to achieve a breakthrough to present political deadlock
and end partisan infighting with full sincerity.
</P>
<P>
In the coming year, Chang said the Cabinet will give priority to
realizing four major policy goals, namely increase investment in
Taiwan, create new jobs, narrow urban-rural disparity as well as
wealth gaps, while upholding the core values of Taiwan-centric
consciousness and social justice.
</P>
<P>
On the domestic political reform, Chang said major tasks will
include government restructuring, upgrading local governments'
powers and capacity, expanding political participation by
perfecting the referendum system and promoting lobbying
legislation.
</P>
<P>
The work agenda will also include promoting taxation reform to
ensure a balance in government finance, accelerating banking
reform, strengthening supervision of corporate management, paving
the way for implementation of the 12-year compulsory education
system, promoting a national pension system, improving welfare
services for the elderly, establishing a sound environmental
impact assessment system and promoting reduction of greenhouse
gas emissions.
</P>
